## Future Enhancements
- Add file handling for persistent data storage.
- Extend system with exam schedules and student profiles.
- Improve input validation and error handling.
- Develop a graphical user interface.

## Conclusion
The DSA-Based Interactive University Assistant successfully applies fundamental data structures to manage university information in a structured and efficient manner.
  The project highlights the practical importance of linked lists, queues, and stacks while providing a simple and interactive academic management tool.
  Its modular design allows easy future expansion and improvement.

